President Trump has declared a major disaster in Massachusetts due to a severe winter storm and snowstorm that occurred in March 2018. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement recovery efforts in the affected areas. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, snow removal, and hazard mitigation measures. James N. Russo has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations. Further designations may be made based on damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.